---+++ configure-misci.sh

Instructions say to use the --choose-user switch to specify the local account for running the MIS-CI cron jobs. Is this the same account as for the mis VO?&lt;br/&gt;
Answer is that it can be the same account as for the mis VO. See [[http://www.ppdg.net/cgi-bin/roundup.cgi/osg-csc/issue9][CSC issue9]].

I ran &lt;br/&gt;&lt;tt&gt;configure-misci.sh --choose-user someacct&lt;/tt&gt; &lt;br/&gt;and there were no complaints until
is said &lt;br/&gt;&lt;tt&gt;ivdgl does not exist&lt;br/&gt;
Please create the user ivdgl and ...&lt;br/&gt;
Or use the option --choose_user ...&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
It would be nice if the script complains about invalid options, like using &#39;-&#39; rather than &#39;_&#39;.

The VOs put into $VDT_LOCATION/MIS-CI/etc/misci/mis-ci-site-info.cfg is not the same as listed on the main instructions page [[Documentation.OsgCEInstallGuide][OSG 0.2.1]].  I guess they should be the same for the default installation.

After running the &lt;tt&gt;run-mis-ci.sh&lt;/tt&gt; I do the &lt;br/&gt;
&lt;tt&gt;globus-job-run &lt;hostname&gt;/jobmanager-mis /bin/sh &quot;siteinfo&quot; &lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
and the output seems to look good, except the line&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;tt&gt;hostname                 localhost&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Should it really say localhost?

